{{notability|Web|date=May 2018}} '''Weblio''' ({{nihongo2|ウェブリオ}}) is a free integrated [[bilingual dictionary]] and [[online encyclopedia]] for Japanese-speaking sites operated by the Weblio Corporation.<ref>{{citation|title=Japanese Language: Reference: Encyclopedias |publisher=[[University of Washington Libraries]]|url=http://guides.lib.uw.edu/c.php?g=342139&p=2302813}}</ref> Weblio can perform a bulk search on a variety of dictionaries, encyclopedias and glossaries, and return results. The dictionary facility includes ''[[Kenkyūsha's New Japanese-English Dictionary]]'' and 70 other Japanese-English and English-Japanese dictionaries with 4,160,000 English words and 4,730,000 Japanese words.<ref name=Stanford/> As of January 20, 2016, a total of 665 dictionaries, encyclopedias and glossary sites can be searched in full.<ref name="home">{{cite web|url=http://www.weblio.jp/|title=Weblio homepage|accessdate=2016-01-20}}</ref>
==History== [[Beta testing]] began on December 12, 2005,<ref name="beta">{{cite web|url=http://www.weblio.jp/company/pr/20051212.jsp|title=プレスリリース オンライン百科事典「Weblio:ウェブリオ」のベータ版をオープン|trans-title=Weblio opens beta version|type=press release|publisher=Weblio|date=2005-12-12|accessdate=2008-01-28}}</ref> and the site began to formally provide services searching 11 different dictionaries and encyclopedias on January 25, the following year.<ref name="open">{{cite web|url=http://www.weblio.jp/company/pr/20060125.jsp|title=プレスリリース オンライン百科事典「Weblio:ウェブリオ」を正式オープン|trans-title=Weblio officially open|publisher=Weblio|type=press release|date=2006-01-25|accessdate=2008-01-28}}</ref>
